Go to <em><strong><span style="color: #000000;">Appearance &gt; Customize &gt; Site Identity</span>.</strong></em> Then Select an image as site icon. It's recommended to use a <strong><em>.ico</em></strong>image as the site icon (favicon).

<a href="https://wordpress-theme.spider-themes.net/docy/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/favicon-2.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2218 size-full" src="https://wordpress-theme.spider-themes.net/docy/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/favicon-2.png" alt="" width="461" height="501" /></a>

&nbsp;

You can configure the footer area of the theme from the settings option. You will find all relevant section settings to the "Footer" option. Navigate to<strong>Theme Options &gt; Footer Settings</strong>to go to this settings section. We provided all necessary instructions and descriptions with all the options.

